  <p>
    The Independent School of Jakarta is proud to announce that Intan Dewiyani, one of the school's exceptional teaching assistants, has been shortlisted for the 2025 Tes Awards for International Schools in the prestigious Teaching Assistant/Support Staff of the Year category.
  </p>

  <p>
    The Tes Awards for International Schools honour outstanding achievements across global education communities. Being shortlisted is a significant accomplishment, placing Intan among an elite group of international educators celebrated for their dedication, innovation, and impact. The full shortlist was formally announced by Tes on Monday, 10 November 2025.
  </p>

  <h2>A Tireless Contribution to ISJ</h2>

  <p>
    Intan's nomination reflects the tireless commitment and professionalism she brings to ISJ every day. Her ability to support students with compassion, skill, and creativity has made her an invaluable part of the school's learning environment, and her impact is felt across classrooms, year groups, and the wider school community.
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    <p>"We are delighted to see Intan recognised on the global stage. Her dedication to supporting student learning and wellbeing is truly inspiring, and we are incredibly proud to have her as part of our ISJ community."</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p class="text-[length:var(--text-xs)] text-charcoal-muted -mt-4 mb-6">Eileen Fisher, Head of School</p>

  <h2>Winners Announced Later This Year</h2>

  <p>
    Winners will be revealed at the international awards ceremony later this academic year. ISJ warmly congratulates Intan on this outstanding achievement and thanks her for her ongoing contribution to the school.
  </p>

</ArticleLayout>
